{"id": 100548, "acmi_id": "181513", "title": "Dorothy Arzner and the boom mic", "title_annotation": "", "slug": "dorothy-arzner-and-the-boom-mic", "creator_credit": "", "credit_line": "", "headline_credit": "", "thumbnail": {"image_url": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P180371_G081.jpg.1200x1200_q85.jpg", "has_video": false}, "record_type": "group", "type": "Object", "is_on_display": true, "last_on_display_place": "ACMI: Gallery 1", "last_on_display_date": "2031-02-16", "is_context_indigenous": false, "material_description": "", "unpublished": false, "first_production_date": null, "brief_description": "<p>Director Dorothy Arzner had a problem on the set of The Wild Party (1929). Her lead actress, silent-era ‘It’ girl Clara Bow, couldn’t perform energetically with the new microphones. To let her move freely, Arzner created the first boom mic.</p>", "constellations_primary": [{"id": 38, "name": "Boom mics, Clara Bow and musicals", "description": "The microphone was called the \"terror of the studios\" when sound films were introduced in the late 1920s, but after initial resistance Hollywood fully embraced the new technology."}], "constellations_other": [], "recommendations": [], "title_for_label": "<p>Dorothy Arzner and the boom mic</p>", "creator_credit_for_label": "", "headline_credit_for_label": "", "description": "<p>Director Dorothy Arzner had a problem on the set of <i>The Wild Party</i> (1929). Her lead actress, silent-era ‘It’ girl Clara Bow, was having trouble transitioning to talkies. Bow was famous for her energetic, flapper-style performances, which she couldn’t do while being still for the microphone to record her dialogue. To let Clara move freely, Arzner rigged a microphone to a fishing rod and created the first ever boom mic. It wasn’t Arzner’s only achievement: <i>The Wild Party</i> was the first talkie directed by a woman, and she was the first female member of the Directors Guild of America – not to mention she made over 40 films during her illustrious career.</p>", "description_for_label": ["<p>Director Dorothy Arzner had a problem on the set of <i>The Wild Party</i> (1929). Her lead actress, silent-era ‘It’ girl Clara Bow, was having trouble transitioning to talkies. Bow was famous for her energetic, flapper-style performances, which she couldn’t do while being still for the microphone to record her dialogue. To let Clara move freely, Arzner rigged a microphone to a fishing rod and created the first ever boom mic. It wasn’t Arzner’s only achievement: <i>The Wild Party</i> was the first talkie directed by a woman, and she was the first female member of the Directors Guild of America – not to mention she made over 40 films during her illustrious career.</p>"], "credit_line_for_label": "", "details": [{"label": "Curatorial section", "display_values": ["The Story of the Moving Image&nbsp;→ Moving Pictures&nbsp;→ 05. Sound and Colour&nbsp;→ MI-05-C02"]}], "stats": {"tap_count": 1961}, "links": [], "creators_primary": [], "creators_other": [], "video_links": [], "media_note": null, "images": [{"id": 13072, "image_file": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P180371_G081.jpg", "image_file_thumbnail": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P180371_G081.jpg.1200x1200_q85.jpg", "image_file_xs": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P180371_G081.jpg.480x480_q85.jpg", "image_file_s": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P180371_G081.jpg.960x960_q85.jpg", "image_file_m": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P180371_G081.jpg.1920x1920_q85.jpg", "image_file_l": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P180371_G081.jpg.3840x3840_q85.jpg", "caption": "", "credit_line": "", "alt_text": "", "width": 2424, "height": 3330, "access_level": "View anywhere"}, {"id": 13073, "image_file": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P180372_G082.jpg", "image_file_thumbnail": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P180372_G082.jpg.1200x1200_q85.jpg",